	<logo>https://static.globalissues.org/i/globalissues/logo-feed.jpg</logo><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40334</id><title>Gaza: Access to key water facility in Khan Younis disrupted, UN reports</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40334" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/16-05-2025-UNNews-Gaza-Displacement02.JPG/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/16-05-2025-UNNews-Gaza-Displacement02.JPG/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A key water reservoir serving Khan Younis in southern Gaza has become inaccessible following new Israeli displacement orders, sparking fears of a collapse in the city’s water distribution network and worsening already dire humanitarian conditions, the United Nations warned on Wednesday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40334&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza: Access to key water facility in Khan Younis disrupted, UN reports”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/16-05-2025-UNNews-Gaza-Displacement02.JPG/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40333</id><title>Adhering to bans on mines only in peace time will not work: UN rights chief</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40333" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/30-06-2025-WFP-Ukraine-04.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/30-06-2025-WFP-Ukraine-04.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The UN’s top human rights official on Wednesday expressed grave alarm that six European countries are either in the process of or are considering withdrawing from the international treaty prohibiting anti-personnel mines. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40333&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Adhering to bans on mines only in peace time will not work: UN rights chief”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/30-06-2025-WFP-Ukraine-04.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40332</id><title>Space is not the final frontier – it is the foundation of our future: UN deputy chief</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40332" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/assets/2018/06/18-06-2018-UNISPACE-50-NASA-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/assets/2018/06/18-06-2018-UNISPACE-50-NASA-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Space technologies are no longer a distant frontier but a critical foundation for daily life and global development, the UN Deputy Secretary-General said on Wednesday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40332&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Space is not the final frontier – it is the foundation of our future: UN deputy chief”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/assets/2018/06/18-06-2018-UNISPACE-50-NASA-02.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40331</id><title>Haitian capital ‘paralysed and isolated’ by gang violence, Security Council hears</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40331" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/15-08-2024-UNOCHA-Haiti-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/15-08-2024-UNOCHA-Haiti-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;More than 1.3 million people have been displaced in Haiti as surging gang violence, lawlessness, and impunity expose the population – especially women and girls – to heightened risks of exploitation and sexual violence. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40331&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Haitian capital ‘paralysed and isolated’ by gang violence, Security Council hears”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/15-08-2024-UNOCHA-Haiti-01.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40330</id><title>INTERVIEW: Sevilla ‘a critical test’ of multilateralism</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40330" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/01-07-2025-UN-News-FFD4-Sevilla-01.jpg/image1440x560cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/01-07-2025-UN-News-FFD4-Sevilla-01.jpg/image1440x560cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Nations taking part in a flagship UN conference have pledged to address the debt crisis in the Global South and boost sustainable development. However, the real test will be whether or not these commitments will be translated into action.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40330&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “INTERVIEW: Sevilla ‘a critical test’ of multilateralism”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/01-07-2025-UN-News-FFD4-Sevilla-01.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40329</id><title>Sevilla: Without sustainable development, there is neither hope nor security</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40329" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/02-07-25_Marcos_Neto_UNDP_Seville_Conference.jpeg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/02-07-25_Marcos_Neto_UNDP_Seville_Conference.jpeg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A senior UN official has told UN News that the global development challenge is not lack of money, but how to align public and private capital flows. The Sevilla Agreement adopted this week, sets out a roadmap for all UN Member States — except the US which pulled out earlier this month — with the aim of mobilizing that capital.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40329&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Sevilla: Without sustainable development, there is neither hope nor security”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/02-07-25_Marcos_Neto_UNDP_Seville_Conference.jpeg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40328</id><title>Drowning in debt: New forum in Sevilla offers borrowers chance to rebalance the books</title><updated>2025-07-02T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40328" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/02-07-2025-UN-News-FFD4.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/02-07-2025-UN-News-FFD4.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A new mechanism offering debt-distressed countries a way to coordinate action and amplify their voice in the global financial system, has been launched at the UN’s pivotal sustainable development conference in Sevilla. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/02/40328&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Drowning in debt: New forum in Sevilla offers borrowers chance to rebalance the books”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/02-07-2025-UN-News-FFD4.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40327</id><title>General Assembly approves $5.4 billion UN peacekeeping budget for 2025-2026</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40327" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-02-2022_UNICEF_DRC-2.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-02-2022_UNICEF_DRC-2.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The General Assembly on Monday approved a $5.38 billion budget for UN peacekeeping operations for the 2025-2026 fiscal year, down slightly from the previous year, as delegates wrapped up weeks of negotiations amid warnings about persistent funding challenges.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40327&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “General Assembly approves $5.4 billion UN peacekeeping budget for 2025-2026”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-02-2022_UNICEF_DRC-2.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40326</id><title>Gaza: Families deprived of the means for survival, humanitarians warn</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40326" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/26-06-2025-UNRWA-Gaza-07.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/26-06-2025-UNRWA-Gaza-07.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The United Nations on Tuesday reported that humanitarian operations in Gaza are facing escalating strain, as ongoing fuel shortages, access restrictions and military activity continue to undermine aid delivery and essential services. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40326&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza: Families deprived of the means for survival, humanitarians warn”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/26-06-2025-UNRWA-Gaza-07.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40325</id><title>Sudan: UN warns of soaring displacement and looming floods</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40325" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/08-04-2025-UNOCHA-Sudan-12.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/08-04-2025-UNOCHA-Sudan-12.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;UN humanitarians on Tuesday sounded the alarm over worsening humanitarian conditions in Sudan, as escalating violence continues to displace civilians and the rising risk of severe flooding during the current rainy season. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40325&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Sudan: UN warns of soaring displacement and looming floods”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/08-04-2025-UNOCHA-Sudan-12.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry></feed><!-- 0.0019s -->